issue.body:
### Checklist

- [X] I'm requesting a site-specific feature
- [X] I've verified that I'm running yt-dlp version **2022.06.22.1** ([update instructions](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp#update)) or later (specify commit)
- [X] I've checked that all provided URLs are playable in a browser with the same IP and same login details
- [X] I've searched the [bugtracker](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/issues?q=) for similar issues including closed ones. DO NOT post duplicates
- [X] I've read the [guidelines for opening an issue](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#opening-an-issue)
- [X] I've read about [sharing account credentials](https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#are-you-willing-to-share-account-details-if-needed) and I'm willing to share it if required

### Region

Europe

### Example URLs

https://www.tiktok.com/@laurenolphert2/video/7082427877588798725

### Description

On sites such as musicaldown.com (among many similar ones), you have the option to download HD version of any TikTok video, that usually has 6x times the bitrate than the best version downloaded by yt-dlp. You can check the [ example URL ](https://www.tiktok.com/@laurenolphert2/video/7082427877588798725) - the best yt-dlp can do is ~2mb without watermark and the HD version from musicaldown is nearly 10 times that at 20mb. also, ~500kb overall bitrate vs ~5700kb for the HD version.

review.body:
## Pull Request Overview

This PR updates the fhir-to-csv package and related code to support Excel output formats alongside CSV/TSV. It adjusts import paths, updates asynchronous API calls to synchronous ones where applicable, and integrates new Excel writer logic throughout streaming and conversion files.
- Update of the fhir-to-csv dependency and related import paths
- Addition of new functionality for handling Excel responses in both production and tests
- Minor refactoring in documentation and JSDoc comments

### Reviewed Changes

Copilot reviewed 24 out of 24 changed files in this pull request and generated no comments.

<details>
<summary>Show a summary per file</summary>

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| src/utils/buffer_to_chunk_transfer_response.js | Changed from using Buffer.slice to Buffer.subarray and updated return types |
| src/tests/.../*.test.js | Adjusted test cases to extract filenames properly and swapped out JSZip for fflate in CSV tests |
| src/operations/summary/summary.js | Added handling for Practitioner summaries |
| src/operations/streaming/resourceWriters/fhirResourceWriterFactory.js | Added branching for Excel content type and integration of the new Excel writer |
| src/operations/streaming/resourceWriters/fhirResourceExcelWriter.js | New file implementing Excel resource writing via conversion and buffered chunk transfers |
| src/converters/bundleToExcelConverter.js, bundleToCsvConverter.js, baseBundleConverter.js | Updated synchronous conversion calls in line with the new package version and updated documentation comments |
| package.json | Upgraded the fhir-to-csv package and replaced JSZip with fflate along with updating XLSX dependency |
</details>



<details>
<summary>Comments suppressed due to low confidence (1)</summary>

**src/operations/streaming/resourceWriters/fhirResourceExcelWriter.js:125**
* There is an inconsistency in property naming: 'this.RequestId' is used here, but 'this.requestId' is used when setting headers. Please standardize the property name to avoid potential bugs.
```
const filename = (this.RequestId ? String(this.RequestId) : generateUUID()) + '.xlsx';
```
</details>
